snippet.textDisplay: The world has enough K.D, Jeff and Rufus covers and after a while one gets jaded. But tailoring a set of words to another brilliant instrumental ( Ode to...) and weaving an absolutely beautiful melody overlaid with a subtle hint of the old pentatonics, now that is music. To all who wish this was a derivative cover of the others, better an original blunder than a borrowed fix. ( Not implied in any way that this cover was a blunder)

snippet.textDisplay: I am a huge Coke Studio fan and a huge fan of "Hallelujah". But personally I didn't think this particular version works. Not if you have listened to the actual song a thousand times like I and many others have. Not saying that a good fusion remix version cannot be made of "Hallelujiah" .....but may be not this one. I would suggest people listen to the Jeff Buckley or the K D Lang version.....especially the K D Lang version. I get goosebumps every time I listen to it.....even after many many times! But then again its all down to personal tastes.

snippet.textDisplay: This song gives me chills, don't get me wrong. And I'm a HUGE fan of Shilpa Rao, favorite singer hands down. But, is it just me, or does the combination just not work? It's like her part is purposely written off key, either that or her melody just does not mesh with the 'Hallelujah' part of the song. I've really tried to get into these Coke Studios, but at the end of the day all the songs are really wierdly written, though nicely performed by brilliant (Trivedi, Karsh, Salim, Kailash) musicians.
